&gt; --- In archive-crawler@yahoogroups.com, Noah Levitt&lt;nlevitt@...&gt;  wrote:
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; Hello Tom,
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; Not sure I fully understand what you&#39;re trying to accomplish. Do you
&gt;&gt; want to follow all links? In that case, change the initial
&gt;&gt; RejectDecideRule in your scope to an AcceptDecideRule. Do you want to
&gt;&gt; crawl links one hop off from the initial sites? Then you may want to try
&gt;&gt; alsoCheckVia. Or are you trying to do something more complicated, like
&gt;&gt; dns lookups for all offsite links, even if the links themselves are not
&gt;&gt; crawled? In that case you might need to write a custom extractor and
&gt;&gt; perhaps custom scope rules as well.
&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt; Noah
&gt;&gt;
